choices.text:
no one is taking us seriously. People think that because we are from low caste, we don't deserve or have right for learning any advanced or in demand course.

I've got the support from my family, but every time i tried to get the admission in colleges, every colleges are telling me that I cannot because of my Caste/Dalit.

The rules are rigged against us from the first page we started the study. Question Papers we got are more difficult then the others. The rules of other colleges and universities restrict us from applying. We are not be a part of concentration classes and if by chance they make us to take those classes we are separated into mass and some are even rejected just like before. Even if we go for distance education, the 'Caste system' follow these colleges too. WE might be able to study in College, but i know that everyone will laugh at us.

Some of my friends who are suffering in the same plight pleads not to reveal my name and give comments. But I want to say that I'm really very tough to learn and I'm not going to get tied up by one 'Caste system'. I want to show all those rich and elite people that we Dalits can also be one of those elite people. I want justice. I don't want them to do anything for us anymore. We'll get what we want all by ourselves.

I'm just using my own voice to tell to everyone all around the world.
